HEADWORD: Tatta
<hw>Tat"ta</hw> <pr>(t⟦acr⟧t"t⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Hind. <ets>⟦tsdot⟧a⟦tsdot⟧⟦tsdot⟧⟦imac⟧</ets>,
<ets>t⟦amac⟧t⟦imac⟧</ets>.]</ety> <def>A bamboo frame or trellis hung at
a door or window of a house, over which water is suffered to trickle, in
order to moisten and cool the air as it enters.</def>
<mark>[India]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

